summary.en-US: We are proud to launch our website [lubdhok07foundation.org](https://lubdhok07foundation.org). This website will serve visitors with our latest activities and contact information.

name.en-US: Lubdhok '07 Contributed to BUET Alumni Association

summary.en-US: As our first community engagement, we collaborated with BUET Alumni Association and contributed to the fund maintained by them. BUET Alumni Association have been working hard during this pandemic, and we are grateful to associate ourselves with their philanthorpy.

name.en-US: Lubdhok'07 Foundation Comes in Aid of Flood-affected People

summary.en-US: Lubdhok'07 Foundation have distributed aid to 150 flood-affected families in 2 upazillas. We are eternally grateful to Bondhu Foundation and [Give Bangladesh](https://www.facebook.com/GiveBangladesh/) for letting us contribute to their endeavor.

details.en-US: Alumna of BUET, currently working in RPGCL (A company of Petrobangla), designated as Assistant Engineer (LNG). She started her organizational voluntary work during her undergraduate studies with CommunityAction, a student-run registered social service organization, and engaged herself in several projects.

Currently working as Area Manager at Berger Paints Bangladesh Ltd in Sales & Marketing department. Enthusiastic about current technology & marketing trends. Passionate to make change and create a long term impact on society through the synergy of working alongside mass people.

content.value: To bring all the alumni of Bangladesh University of Engineering & Technology (BUET) batch 2007 on a common platform for lending their professional expertise and experience to serve Bangladesh.
To engage in charitable purposes and social welfare activities on a strictly non-profit basis.
To provide aid (financial, technological, and voluntary) to the distressed people in need of education, medical, and financial support.
To Provide relief to the people affected by natural and manmade disasters and assist in their rehabilitation and development.

To provide financial aid and/or loan with prior approval of the members of the executive committee of the Society to the members of the Society and/or their family under the circumstances of emergency medical treatments, bankruptcy, financial crisis due natural disasters, sudden death, etc.
To provide grants, stipends, academic scholarship, and fellowships and to sponsor a significant number of brilliant and poor students based on proper evidence of their needs.
To provide or lend technical support, engineering expertise, and innovative solutions to serve charitable causes and resolve crises.
To cooperate, assist, and engage in joint programs with organizations and agencies seeking relief, rehabilitation, and development in Bangladesh and any purpose aligned with the Society's goals.
To set up educational, health, industrial, business, financial institutions subject to the approval by the benefit of the Society.

To organize appropriate social events and activities such as seminars, meetings, online sessions, conferences, etc. can also cover diverse fields such as art, literature, science, and other knowledge base education.
